node.text:
The Dalmatian pups are getting big. A another 14 pup litter! Bullies are still our primary breed but @mrsbullymarket wanted a Dalmatian so we got a female. At first it was strictly for companionship but once we got ours she was chasing coyotes off our property by the time she was 6 months old.

She almost instantly served a purpose around the ranch and this is an important role here. A few years ago we had a couple bully pups snatched by coyotes. Never to be seen again. Ever since having the Dalmatians roam the property that hasn’t been a problem.

So now we have a few Dalmatians and a litter or two a year to carry on the line and keep some dogs on our ranch. They definitely earn their keep around here. What other breeds do you like besides bullies? 🐾📈

node.text: Introducing Bully Market’s Vision. I don’t think I’ve posted her up yet other than on Snapchat and IG stories so I wanted to give a formal introduction. Vision is a product of our Bando x American Dream breeding (Heavy Bully Market blood). She’s a heavy boned, thick girl, with a compact frame and wide rib cage. Super spunky and outgoing personality. She reminds me of a tri color version her mom. Pictured at about a year old here. Still a lot of maturing to do. 👁🤝📈 #BullyMarketsVision #BullyMarketBloodLine www.BullyMarket.com

node.text: It’s been some years since I’ve been to a dog show and even longer since I’ve judged  but my friend @oscar_gomez_wba brought me out of retirement for this one. I am excited and honored to have been invited to judge at the first WBA event. It’s going down May 22nd and 23rd in Medellin, Colombia! A three show event! Let’s get it, Bully Fam! 🤝📈 @wbaregistryofficialpage #WBA #BullyShow #AmericanBully #Medellin #Colombia #BullyMarket www.BullyMarket.com

node.text: We only got one pup out of the Beastro x Marsha repeat. Definitely wish we would have gotten more but sometimes one is all you need. The first breeding gave us two females. This breeding gave us this beautiful boy. I’m excited to watch him grow. Still not 100% on a name for him yet. For now, we’ve been calling him Lord Archibald. 😁📈 #BeastroXMarsha www.BullyMarket.com
